        <div class="class1">
             <h4>Salabhasana (Locust pose)</h4>
             <ol>
                 <li>Begin on your belly with your feet together and your hands reaching back, palms down.
                 </li>
                 <li>Extend your legs and press down with all ten toenails to activate your quadriceps.</li>
                 <li>Rotate your inner thighs to the ceiling to broaden your lower back.</li>
                 <li>Keeping your hands lightly on the mat, raise your head and chest and your legs, leading with your inner thighs.
                 </li>
                 <li>Roll your shoulders back and up away from the floor. Keep the back of your neck long and emphasize lifting your sternum instead of lifting your chin. Don’t grip your glutes.</li>
                 <li>To come out of the pose, slowly release.</li>
             </ol>
