        <div class="class1">
             <h4>Phalakasana II (Forearm Plank)</h4>
             <ol>
                 <li>Place your forearms onto the floor with your hands shoulder-distance apart and your shoulders stacked above your elbows.
                 </li>
                 <li>Pin your elbows into your midline and engage the external rotators of your shoulders.</li>
                 <li>Step your feet back so your body is long and straight like a plank of wood.</li>
                 <li>Root down with your big toe mounds to engage your quadriceps.
                 </li>
                 <li>Lift the tops of your thighs to the ceiling while descending your tailbone to the floor in order to create a slight posterior tilt in your pelvis and become compact at your center.</li>
                 <li>Your lower belly should feel like a tray supporting your lower back.</li>
                 <li>Extend your sternum forward and press your heels back.</li>
                 <li>Build up to being able to hold for 1 minute at a time.</li>
             </ol>
